<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Achieve" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Achieve,</orth> 1) absol. to make an end, to perform what is intended: <cit><quote>and does a. as soon as draw his sword,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 4.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 7, 23</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) trans. a) to perform, to execute: <cit><quote>which they shall have no sooner --d but we'll set upon them,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.2.193" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 2, 193</bibl></cit>.
<lb />b) to kill, to finish: <cit><quote>bid them a. me,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.3.91" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 3, 91</bibl></cit>.
<lb />c) to gain, to obtain, 1) as the result of exertion: <cit><quote>experience is by industry --d,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.3.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. I, 3, 22</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.1.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 1, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.1.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 1, 20</bibl> <bibl n="shak. shr 1.1.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 1, 20</bibl> <bibl n="shak. shr 1.1.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 1, 20</bibl> <bibl n="shak. shr 1.2.268" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 268</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 1.1.52" default="NO" valid="yes">Alls I, 1, 52</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 2.5.157" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 5, 157</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.47" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 5.378.47" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 378</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.254" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 254</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 4.217.254" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 217</bibl>. H5 Epil. <bibl n="shak. r2 4.217.254" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 217</bibl> <bibl n="shak. cor 1.9.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 9, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.1.80" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 1, 80</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.1.80" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 1, 80</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ant 3.1.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 1, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 5.1.117" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V, 1, 117</bibl>. 2) without the notion of exertion: <cit><quote>that sin by him advantage should a.</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 67.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 67, 3</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>your fortune --d her mistress,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.210" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 2, 210</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.2.105" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 2, 105</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.2.46" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B V, 2, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.61" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 1, 61</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>